PRIVACY NOTICE ON THE USE OF COOKIES OR SIMILAR TECHNOLOGIES
Through this Privacy Notice, we would like to provide you with details regarding the processing of your personal data in the context of placing “cookies” or similar technologies on your device when you access the website www.therme.ro and its related subdomains (the “website”).
We recommend that you read this Privacy Notice together with the Privacy Policy and Cookie Policy, in order to obtain as much information as possible on how we protect your personal data.
WHAT ARE THE CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL DATA?
Cookies do not store personal data that can directly identify you such as first name, last name, address, or other similar data. Cookies may collect the following categories of data:
Device data, such as the IP address and the browser you are using;
Unique ID generated for your device that allows us to distinguish you from other visitors for generating statistical data on how you use the website;
The pages you have accessed on our website, how many times you have accessed those pages, when it was the first and most recent access etc.;
Recording of selected preferences (consent or other available options) and their history;
Preferred settings such as the language or region from which you come;
Bandwidth of the data network you are using.
WHY DO WE PROCESS THIS PERSONAL DATA?
We process this data for purposes such as:
Ensuring functionality and maintaining adequate security of the website;
Fixing technical errors or problems;
Adapting the displayed content according to the device you use and the area from which you access the website;
Recording your preferences when visiting the website;
Obtaining statistical information about how you use the website for the purpose of improving the services;
Marketing and advertising purposes (e.g. providing personalized information according to your preferences).
Therme’s legitimate interests (e.g. registration of consent and marketing options that you accept or decline etc.);
Other similar purposes.
WHAT ARE THE LEGAL GROUNDS ON WHICH WE PROCESS YOUR DATA?
The cookies we use are divided into 4 categories:
Necessary cookies;
Preference cookies;
Statistical cookies;
Marketing cookies.
We process the
strictly necessary cookies
on the basis of our
legitimate interest
to ensure the basic functionality of the website, to ensure its security, as well as compliance with the requirements of data protection laws, for example, when we record your choices regarding the acceptance of cookies or other situations in which you consent. These cookies are automatically placed, but they can be deleted at any time from your browser settings.
Preference, statistical
and
marketing cookies
are only used on the basis of
your consent
depending on the preferences selected in the Cookie Privacy Panel that shows up when you access our website. You may withdraw your consent at any time during the processing.
WHO ELSE HAS ACCESS TO YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
Personal data may also be accessed by other third parties to the extent that this is reasonably necessary in accordance with the purposes set out in this Privacy Notice. For details, please refer to the dedicated section of the Privacy Policy.
Certain cookies may also be placed and managed by third parties such as Google.
HOW DO WE MANAGE INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFER?
We usually process your data within the European Union, but we may also transfer your data to the US or other third countries for which the European Commission has not issued adequacy decisions or appropriate safeguards including binding corporate rules. In these cases, we usually rely on your explicit consent to the transfer of data.
In order to see all the legal conditions under which we may transfer your personal data to these destinations, please refer to the “International data transfer” section of the Privacy Policy.
HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
Depending on the purpose of each cookie, the personal data is kept:
Only for the period of browsing the website pages -
session cookies
, which expire when the browser is closed;
For defined periods (1 day, 1 month, 3 months, 2 years, etc.);
For an indefinite period –
persistent cookies
.
WHAT ARE YOUR RIGHTS?
For the purpose of processing your personal data through cookies you have the following rights:
Right to be informed;
Right of access;
Right to rectification;
Right to erasure, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to restriction of processing;
Right to data portability to another controller, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to object to the processing of your personal data;
Right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects on you or similarly affects you to a significant extent, with the exceptions set out in data protection laws;
The right to withdraw consent at any time;
Right to lodge a complaint with
a supervisory authority.
For detailed information on the use of cookies, changing preferences or withdrawing consent, please visit the cookie Policy.
UPDATING THE PRIVACY NOTICE
The information presented in this Privacy notice will be reviewed periodically to reflect any changes in current processing activities.
Please visit this page periodically to make sure you always have up-to-date information.
However, if we intend to significantly change the way we use your personal data, we will notify you in advance.
Last update:
April 2024
