PRIVACY NOTICE ON MARKETING NOTIFICATIONS
Through this Privacy Notice, we want to provide you with details about the processing of your personal data in the context of the transmission of marketing communications
such as
“newsletter”, “web app”
,
“push App”.
We recommend that you read this Privacy Notice together with the Privacy Policy, in order to obtain as much information as possible on how we protect your personal data.
WHAT ARE THE CATEGORIES OF DATA THAT WE PROCESS?
The personal data processed for the purpose of sending marketing notifications is usually limited to your email address that you provide us when signing up for the newsletter once the MyTherme account is created.
Notifications can be sent both by email and directly to your MyTherme account (which can be accessed both from our website and through the My Therme mobile Apps).
WHY DO WE PROCESS THIS DATA?
The marketing notifications we send to you have the following purposes:
Promoting Therme’s products and services;
Carrying out surveys, market research;
Promoting Therme’s events, marketing campaigns;
Promoting Therme’s image and the group to which it belongs;
Other similar marketing activities.
WHAT ARE THE LEGAL GROUNDS ON WHICH WE PROCESS YOUR DATA?
Marketing communications are always based on your prior consent obtained at the time of the creation of the account, by a separate statement. Giving or withdrawing consent is always freely expressed and it is not conditioned by accepting other terms and conditions.
You can change your marketing options (activation, deactivation, modification) at any time from your My Therme account, in the Settings/ Notifications settings section.
Also, each marketing notification sent to you by email contains an unsubscribe button at the bottom of the email. The withdrawal of consent does not affect the lawfulness of the processing before its withdrawal.
The law aslo allows us to send you notifications for marketing purposes that are based on our legitimate interest, without obtaining your prior consent, for the promotion of products and services similar to those you have previously purchased. If you do not agree with these communications, you can contact us at any time to stop them.
WHO ELSE HAS ACCESS TO YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
Personal data may also be accessed by other third parties to the extent that this is reasonably necessary in accordance with the purposes set out in this notice. Our marketing partners as well as the website developer will mainly have access to this data.
For details, please see the dedicated section of the Privacy Policy.
HOW DO WE MANAGE INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFER?
For this processing activity, your personal data is stored and processed on servers in Romania and the European Union.
HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
We use your email address to send you notifications for as long as you subscribe to the Therme Newsletter, until you withdraw your consent.
In case of withdrawal of consent, your email address will be deleted from our database according to our data storage policy.
The erasure will only take place to the extent that such personal data is no longer necessary for other purposes.
WHAT ARE YOUR RIGHTS?
For the purpose of using your personal data for the transmission of marketing communications, you shall  have the following rights:
Right to be informed;
Right of access;
Right to rectification;
Right to erasure, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to restriction of processing;
Right to data portability to another controller, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to object to the processing of your personal data;
Right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects on you or similarly affects you to a significant extent, with the exceptions set out in data protection laws;
Right to lodge a complaint with
a supervisory authority.
UPDATING THE PRIVACY NOTICE
The information presented in this Privacy notice will be reviewed periodically to reflect any changes in current processing activities.
Please visit this page periodically to make sure you always have up-to-date information.
However, if we intend to significantly change the way we use your personal data, we will notify you in advance.
