PRIVACY NOTICE ON THE INSTALLATION AND USE OF MYTHERME MOBILE APPLICATIONS
Through this Privacy Notice we want to provide you with details about the processing of your personal data in the context of the installation and use of MyTherme mobile applications.
We recommend that you read this Privacy Notice together with the Privacy Policy, in order to obtain as much information as possible on how we protect your personal data.
MyTherme Apps give you the posibility to access our services from mobile devices with iOS and Android operating systems. They allow you to access our web shop and also the content of the website www.therme.ro. and its related subdomains.
This Privacy Notice addresses only specific situations involving the processing of personal data in the context of the installation and use of MyTherme mobile applications.
Information about the use of your MyTherme account, the purchase of products and services, marketing notifications, the receipt and management of your requests, or other activities that may be carried out through the applications is detailed in the different information Notes. Please refer to the “Privacy Notice” section of the Privacy Policy.
WHAT ARE THE CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL DATA THAT WE PROCESS?
When you use MyTherme mobile applications, we may process the following personal data:
The IP of your device;
Device’s operating system;
Type of the device;
The set language of the phone;
Unique ID generated for your device that allows us to distinguish you from other users for generating statistical data on how you use the applications.
Pages accessed, number of visits, etc.;
The region from which you come;
Logs about your actions in the applications;
Errors, changes made successfully etc.
WHY DO WE PROCESS THIS DATA?
We process this data for:
Ensuring functionality and maintaining adequate security throughout the application.
Personalising the display of the content; (e.g. the language in which the information is displayed to you);
Obtaining statistical information and reports about how you use Therme applications for the purpose of improving the services, or other marketing purposes;
Fixing errors or technical issues;
Maintaining adequate security during application use;
Keeping logs about user’s actions, etc.
WHAT TOOLS DO WE USE FOR DATA ANALYTICS?
For traffic analysis we use Google Analytics for applications.
To learn more about what data google analytics collects when you use My Therme apps on both iOS and Android, please visit the link below:
https://firebase.google.com/products/analytics?gclid=Cj0KCQjwmPSSBhCNARIsAH3cYgbgoF2EGoW0usRMmWlFg9QyT7wbs2LUeXooEHv3jA1-U0P5-Za4Qe0aAk0MEALw_wcB&gclsrc=aw.ds
In order to limit the collection of excessive data, we have set Google analytics to collect only those data strictly necessary in relation to the stated purposes.
WHAT ARE THE LEGAL GROUNDS ON WHICH WE PROCESS YOUR DATA?
We rely on our
legitimate interest
when we process your data strictly necessary for the functionality of the application, maintaining an adequate level of security, fixing errors or technical problems, providing legally binding information in the set language of your phone, saving your marketing options, etc. Under these conditions, the information is collected automatically without your consent and is used throughout the use of the application.
We rely on your consent when we process your data for statistical reports on how you use the App, your preferences when you browse the App, or for other similar marketing and advertising purposes.
In this regard, we ask for your consent in advance each time you log into the MyTherme application. For these types of processing, you can withdraw your consent at any time by accessing the privacy section of your account. The withdrawal of consent does not affect the lawfulness of the processing before its withdrawal.
WHO ELSE HAS ACCESS TO YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
Personal data may also be accessed by other third parties, to the extent that this is reasonably necessary in accordance with the purposes set out in this Privacy Notice.
Among them we can mention: Application developers, analytics service providers (e.g. Google), marketing and advertising partners etc.
For details, please refer to the dedicated section of the Privacy Policy.
HOW DO WE MANAGE INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFER?
We usually process your data within the European Union, but we may also transfer your data to the US or other third countries for which the European Commission has not issued adequacy decisions or appropriate safeguards including binding corporate rules. In these cases, we rely on your explicit consent to the transfer of data.
Please refer to the Privacy Policy to learn more about the conditions under which we may transfer data to international destinations.
HOW LONG DO WE PROCESS YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
The data necessary for our
legitimate purposes
are processed throughout the use of the application.
The data collected on the basis of your
consent
is processed throughout the use of the application or until the withdrawal of consent.
In the event of
withdrawal of consent
, we will cease processing your data for the stated purposes.
Alternatively, upon deletion, the collected data may be anonymized, depriving them of their personal character, which makes it impossible to identify you; this allows us to use it for statistical purposes for unlimited periods of time.
Once the application is uninstalled, any subsequent reinstallation will use a new ID to distinguish you from other users. Therefore, we will not be able to know what ID you had before the application was uninstated and the collected information will not be able to be aggregated.
WHAT ARE YOUR RIGHTS?
In the context of using Therme mobile applications, for the above purposes, you have the following rights:
Right to be informed;
Right of access;
Right to rectification;
Right to erasure, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to restriction of processing;
Right to data portability to another controller, under the conditions stipulated by law;
Right to object to the processing of your personal data;
Right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects on you or similarly affects you to a significant extent, with the exceptions set out in data protection laws;
The right to withdraw consent at any time;
Right to lodge a complaint with
a supervisory authority.
AUTOMATED DECISION-MAKING PROCESSES
In our processing activities we do not use automated decision-making or profiling, that may produce legal effects that concern you or that may similarly affect you to a significant extent. The human factor is always involved, in decision-making.
To the extent that it will be necessary to adopt exclusively automated processes, we will ensure that we protect your rights and freedoms and that we comply with all legal data protection requirements.
UPDATING THE PRIVACY NOTICE
The information presented in this Privacy Notice will be reviewed periodically to reflect any changes in current processing activities.
Please visit this page periodically to make sure you always have up-to-date information.
However, if we intend to significantly change the way we use your personal data, we will notify you in advance.
Last update:
April 2024
